Lagos State Assembly has lifted the suspension placed on four of its members. The Speaker, Rt Hon. Mudashiru Obasa made the announcement on Thursday at the start of plenary He said the Governor’s Advisory Council and the National Leader of the All Progressives Congress called a meeting on Tuesday to intervene in the crisis and directed that the House should reinstate the suspended lawmakers. The affected lawmakers are Mr Olumuyiwa Jimoh, who was the former Deputy Majority Leader,  Mr Rotimi Abiru who was the Chief Whip,  Mr Moshood Oshun and Mr Raheem Adewale. Their indefinite suspension was announced at the plenary on Monday, March 9 of this month and the affected lawmakers were since then denied access to the legislative complex. 